channel.description: [size=36pt]This is old, Im going to start fixing it up (for fun), so I felt like reposting.[/size] [center][u][b]What Is Earthscape?[/b][/u] Earthscape is a project i started a while ago, while i had just begun coding runescape private servers. It is a balanced source, with great pking, and also a manageable economy. I was aiming for something that looked earth-like, hence the home in Version one, the training in version 1 and 2, and the pk area, which has been maintained through all 3 versions released so far. It has a unique way of runecrafting, which i have totally integrated into the source, it seems as tho it was a part of the runescape we now emulate. [u][b]What Is So Great About Earthscape?[/b][/u] Earthscape has the following Features - Version 1 - Never Before Seen Home The portals used, had never been used before. Summoning A Never Before Seen Pking Area Never Before Seen Shops New Wyvern Area New dagganoth Area Wishing Well Custom Items (viewable only with silabgarza client) Version 2 - Version 2 was more 1.5, as i only coded a new home, and added more commands,etc New home Fixed some glitches Added a News System New Vengeance Version 3 - Added scoreboard (players online) to home New Veng Complete summoning I cleaned up the client class, along with some others. 2 New Training Area's (::train & ::train2) New Shops I tried to utilize the advice the reaper gave to me, so the training areas are less crowded, i tried it for the shops, but..it didnt really work out. All new runecrafting, totally intergrated into the server, there isnt even an object placed. ( no picture ) For version 3 i created a new vengeance() method, so it freed up some space in the parseincomingpackets method. [center]What Is Earthscape?
Earthscape is a project i started a while ago, while i had just begun coding runescape private servers.
It is a balanced source, with great pking, and also a manageable economy.
I was aiming for something that looked earth-like, hence the home in Version one, the training in version 1 and 2, and the pk area, which has been maintained through all 3 versions released so far.
It has a unique way of runecrafting, which i have totally integrated into the source, it seems as tho it was a part of the runescape we now emulate.

What Is So Great About Earthscape?

Earthscape has the following Features -

Version 1 -

Never Before Seen Home
The portals used, had never been used before.
Summoning
A Never Before Seen Pking Area
Never Before Seen Shops
New Wyvern Area
New dagganoth Area
Wishing Well
Custom Items (viewable only with silabgarza client)

Version 2 -

Version 2 was more 1.5, as i only coded a new home, and added more commands,etc
New home
Fixed some glitches
Added a News System
New Vengeance

Version 3 -
Added scoreboard (players online) to home
New Veng
Complete summoning
I cleaned up the client class, along with some others.
2 New Training Area’s (::train & ::train2)
New Shops
I tried to utilize the advice the reaper gave to me, so the training areas are less crowded, i tried it for the shops, but…it didnt really work out.
All new runecrafting, totally intergrated into the server, there isnt even an object placed. ( no picture )
For version 3 i created a new vengeance() method, so it freed up some space in the parseincomingpackets method. Which means, less work for you
